<table class="metadata plainlinks mbox-small" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9;">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Special:Search/Populism" title="wikt:Special:Search/Populism"><img alt="Sister project" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/40px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png" width="40" height="44" border="0" /></a></td>
<td class="mbox-text" style="">Look up <i><b><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Special:Search/populism" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:Special:Search/populism">populism</a></b></i> in<br />
<a href="/wiki/Wiktionary" title="Wiktionary">Wiktionary</a>, the free dictionary.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Populism</b> is a discourse which claims to support "the people" versus "the elites". Populism may comprise an ideology urging social and political system changes and/or a rhetorical style deployed by members of political or social movements. Generally, populism invokes an idea of democracy as being solely the expression of the people's will.</p>
